description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Break into prison healthcare!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Have you ever thought about working within the prison environment?&lt;br /&gt; Are you looking for a challenging and rewarding role with career development? Then look no further…&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; HMP Huntercombe is a Category C men&#39;s prison, located near Nuffield in Oxfordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So what can we offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We recognise training and development is key, therefore we training centre to facilitate for your needs. You will gain insight and training in Mental Health and Substance Misuse.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; If you are new to offender health, we will create a suitable induction package to ensure you are equipped for this exciting role.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; In this environment we appreciate flexibility around working hours hence we are willing to accommodate part time requests. We offer a competitive annual salary plus payment of MDU/MPS subscription and CPD days. Furthermore should you wish there are plenty of opportunities for extra shifts and overtime.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We also offer company benefits and schemes including company contributory pension scheme, 25 days annual leave plus 8 public bank holidays, staff well-being, access to bank hours, cycle to work scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relocation to be considered for permanent employees. This can be discussed at interview stage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Multi-Disciplinary Team, the General Practitioner will provide clinical assessment and diagnosis to patient’s requirements and make timely decisions regarding future management. You will also provide a highly specialist resource to other healthcare staff, patients and carers and have active involvement in clinical governance/effectiveness activities.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; It doesn’t end there; you will have a chance to become actively involved in audit, teaching and training (management of substance misuse and/or blood borne viruses) as well as helping us to adapt the service to the ever-changing needs of the patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Job Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MBChB or MBBS qualified, you’ll be registered with the GMC and on a PCT Medical Performers List. RCGP1 part 1 is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Further Job Information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This permanent salaried post working 37.5 hours per week at £105,000 per annum.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Please note that this role is subject to Practice Plus Group Terms &amp; Conditions and offers of employment are subject to satisfactory receipt of references, enhanced DBS check and prison vetting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
